# 7. みんなとちょっとだけ暗い森

An: I'm so sorry, Kohane! I had no idea that it was you inside that mask. Honestly, me running from you like that...
Kohane: No, it's okay! I'm sorry for chasing after you the way I did. I feel awful about making you feel so scared...
An: That's totally fine! If anything, it ended up being good exercise!
Akito: Seriously, how did things end up like this...?
Toya: But I'm glad that we were able to meet up. We can finally start seeing what your School Festival has to offer.
Akito: So, what do you wanna do? You still up for going inside this haunted house?
An: O-Of course I'm going in...! Kohane and her class worked really hard on it!
An: I-I'm a little scared... B-But I'll be fine!
Kohane: An...
Kohane: Thank you... Fortunately, I have a feeling that you're going to like our haunted house...
Kohane: Because there's a way for you to enjoy it as a game.
An: R-Really? What about that scary wolf?
Kohane: Some other girls from my class made that and it's really only meant for guests who seem like thrill seekers. So, it's not like you'll have a bunch of those chasing after you.
Toya: Does that mean the wolves inside will look a bit more standard?
Akito: I kinda wanted to see the scary one in action... But I'm also kinda curious to see how they toned it down for the fraidy cats.
Kohane: Don't worry! It's meant to be fun for everyone!
Kohane: So, I hope you guys enjoy it...
An: Kohane...
An: Okay... Then... Let's go in!
Receptionist: Alright, we have four entering the forest!
Receptionist: But before you go, you'll get to choose to wear one of three hats! You can be Little Red Riding Hood, a young goat or a hunter!
An: Hats...? What happens when we wear these?
Kohane: Oh, how you go through the haunted house changes based on which you choose.
Kohane: If you're Little Red Riding Hood or a goat, it'll be a maze like a normal haunted house, and your goal will be to reach the exit.
Kohane: If you choose to be a hunter, you'll be given a toy gun that lets you shoot and chase away wolves.
Kohane: Whenever you feel like you're in danger, all you have to do is point your gun at a wolf and say, “Bang!” Then it'll go away.
Toya: I see... Is this what you meant by enjoying this haunted house as a game, Azusawa?
Toya: At the same time, I feel that things would become too unbalanced if we all choose to be hunters.
Kohane: Oh, actually, only one person per group can choose to be a hunter. The rest will become Little Red Riding Hood or goats.
Akito: Then, An, you should be our hunter. You'd feel better if you knew you could fight back, right?
Toya: Alright, Azusawa, you'll be our Little Red Riding Hood. Akito and I will be the goats.
An: Y-You can count on me! I'll blast anything scary that comes our way...!
Kohane: Okay! Plus...
Kohane: If things get really scary, An, I'll be there to protect you!
An: ...! Okay! Thanks, Kohane!
An: I-It's pretty dark in here...! But some of these decorations are pretty cute...
Toya: Yes, they did a good job of making it feel like a fairytale.
An: Yeah, I should be able to handle...
Rin: <Whoa! Kohane, is this your haunted house?!>
An: Eep! M-Monster! My gun! Where's my gun?!
Kohane: An... That was just Rin!
An: Huh? O-Oh, you're right... Sorry about that, Rin...
Akito: Relax, will you...?
Toya: Also, we're blocking the entrance, so we should probably proceed.
An: W-Wait! We should stick together and...
???: *Howl*
An: *Scream*
???: *Growl* *Howl*
An: W-Wolf! I have to... Wait, huh?
Mischievous Wolf: *Bark* *Howl*
Akito: It's acting kinda goofy...
Mischievous Wolf: Hm?! *Howl*
Toya: It's raising its arms. Is it trying to intimidate us?
Akito: I've seen a different animal do this before... Red pandas, I think?
Mischievous Wolf: *Whimper*
An: Haha...! It's actually kinda cute!
Kohane: (*Gasp* Thank goodness! An's smiling!)
Kohane: (I'm so glad that I asked Minori to be a cute wolf for us...!)
An: Bye bye, Wolfie!
Mischievous Wolf: Woof♪
Akito: Alright, that wolf seemed pretty friendly...
An: Yeah, I feel a lot better now! This much I can handle!
Kohane: Hehe. Great!
An: So, let's keep going!
Unfettered Wolf: *Howl* *Snarl*
An: Wh-What's going on?! That wolf seems pretty wild!
Kohane: An, your gun! Now's your chance!
An: O-Oh, right! Bang!
Unfettered Wolf: *Whimper*
Rin: <You did it! An, that was so cool!>
An: Hehe. You think so?
Cute Wolf: *Howl*
Toya: This one seems much cuter. However, it doesn't seem like it's about to let us pass.
An: Heh heh heh. Just leave that to me. Bang!
Cute Wolf: *Whimper*
An: How's that? I feel like a pro now.
Kohane: Yeah, An, you're doing great!
An: This is so much fun! It really feels like a video game! I was kinda scared of them jumping out at first, but I've gotten the hang of shooting them!
An: I can probably handle whatever this place throws at me now!
Toya: It's good to see that you're enjoying yourself, Shiraishi.
Akito: I mean, this is pretty mellow as far as haunted houses go. I guess this is about the level An can really handle.
Toya: Speaking of which, Akito, you don't seem all that bothered by the wolves.
Akito: That's because I know they're not real. Especially the ones that look goofy and cartoonish. Those aren't gonna...
???: ...
???: *Growl*
An: Uhh... That one sounded pretty real... Was that...?
Toya: A real wolf...?
Kohane: (I asked Shiho to do a little surprise for us since some of us don't seem to be scared easily, like Shinonome.)
Toya: Hmm... These trees seem much more realistic. Your class has done an excellent job of recreating a dusky forest.
An: B-But I have a feeling that something's about to...
???: *Growl*
An: *Gasp* That sound...
Zombie Wolf: *Bark*
An & Akito: Eep!!! Whoa!!!
An: W-W-W-Wait a second! That's the zombie wolf Kohane was playing earlier, right?!
Akito: Its fangs look real...
Toya: Try to calm down, Akito, Shiraishi. You said just now that it's not real, yes?
Akito: Y-Yeah, I know! A-An!!! Shoot it so we can...
An: I... I... I...! I know! But my hands are shaking too much!
Akito: Huh?!
Kohane: Oh no...!
Kohane: An! Pass me that gun!
An: K-Kohane...?!
Kohane: Here, put on my hat!
An: O-Okay...!
Rin: <Cool! You can do it, Kohane!>
Kohane: So... I aim the gun at the wolf and...
Kohane: Fire...! Bang! Bang!
Zombie Wolf: Guh...!
An: Hey, I think you stunned it...
Toya: Is this our chance to head towards the exit?
Kohane: Let's go, you guys!
An: Geez, that was scary... My heart's still racing...
Akito: Yeah, I feel pretty tired...
Kohane: Hehe. Me too... And it was my first time going in as a guest. That was really thrilling.
Kohane: So, how was it...? Did you guys have fun...?
An: Yeah!
An: It was super fun! I don't think I've ever seen a haunted house like this one before!
An: It was scary... But that wasn't a problem because you were there to protect me in the end, Kohane!
Toya: I enjoyed it as well. I didn't realize haunted houses could be so much fun.
Akito: Yeah, our class did a slightly better one, but we never would've been able to put anything together like that last wolf...
Kohane: *Gasp* Thank goodness...!
Shiho: Sounds like you all enjoyed yourselves.
Minori: Hehe. I'm so glad for you, Kohane!
Kohane: Oh, Minori, Shiho!
Kohane: Yeah, we did! Thank you both for helping me out!
An: Wait, does that mean...? Were you both the wolves?
Minori: Yup! I was the one that appeared in the beginning, and Shiho was the last one.
An: What? That really scary one was you, Hinomori? Wow... You put on a really good performance.
Shiho: Oh, I just tried copying how a real wolf howls... The wolf's head I think did the rest.
Toya: Yes, that mask is quite something. Even when Azusawa was wearing it, I felt that it belonged in a horror film.
Akito: Yeah, I get what you mean... But did you guys have to make it look so realistic?
Shiho: Interesting... I guess you're not as tough as you look.
Akito: What? Hey, don't get the wrong idea.
An: Haha! You did great too, Akito! Anyway, Hinomori, Minori, thanks a bunch!
Kohane: Hehe...
Kohane: (I really wasn't sure what was gonna happen when I had to go chase after An...)
Kohane: (But I'm so glad we're smiling like this now.)
